        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer596039620" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10221362558105568182">A slow-paced crime novel set in rural Georgia before the First World War. Little girls are gruesomely murdered, impacting the life and future of Joseph Vaughan, precocious teenager. It is slow going. A better writer would have gotten away with it, but Ellory&apos;s prose is over-the-top and repetitive, trying too hard to be poignant and poetic. Joseph&apos;s obsession with the murders and subsequent navel gazing might have been interesting had there been som depth to it, but he remains a two-dimensional c</span>
  <span id="freeText10221362558105568182" style="display:none">A slow-paced crime novel set in rural Georgia before the First World War. Little girls are gruesomely murdered, impacting the life and future of Joseph Vaughan, precocious teenager. It is slow going. A better writer would have gotten away with it, but Ellory's prose is over-the-top and repetitive, trying too hard to be poignant and poetic. Joseph's obsession with the murders and subsequent navel gazing might have been interesting had there been som depth to it, but he remains a two-dimensional character and the endless dwelling grows infuriating after a few hundred pages. The novel tries to be something it is not, and would have been better off as a straight-forward crime story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10221362558105568182" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


